olive oil
2 potato
1 carrot
1 leek
1 bag baby broccoli
1 bag thyme
½ packet panko breadcrumbs
1 packet chicken breast
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 packet Onion Chutney
10 g butter
½ cup water
1 sachet Gravy Granules
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into bite-sized chunks.
• Place potato on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with
olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice carrot into sticks. Thinly
slice leek.
• Halve any thick baby broccoli lengthways.
• Pick thyme leaves. In a medium bowl, combine
panko breadcrumbs (see ingredients), grated
Parmesan cheese, thyme and a drizzle of
olive oil.

• Cut deep slices, taking care to not slice all the
way through, across chicken breast in 1cm
intervals.
• Place chicken on a second lined oven tray,
sprinkle with garlic & herb seasoning, drizzle
with olive oil and toss to coat.
• Spoon onion chutney over the chicken, then
top with cheesy panko mix.
• Place chicken on the lower oven shelf and bake
until cooked through, 12-16 minutes.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it is no longer
pink inside.

• When potatoes have 10 minutes remaining, heat
a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a
drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook carrot, baby broccoli and leek until
tender, 5-7 minutes.
• Add the butter, season and toss to coat. Transfer
to a bowl and cover to keep warm.

• Wipe out the frying pan and return to
medium-high heat.
• Add the water and gravy granules and whisk
until smooth and slightly thickened,
2-3 minutes.

• Divide onion chutney and Parmesan crumbed
chicken, roast potatoes and buttery veggies
between plates.
• Spoon gravy over potatoes to serve. Enjoy!